@startuml Temperature Update Flow — MVVM LVGL Observer

skinparam backgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #444444
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBorderColor #CCCCCC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam shadowing false

actor        User
participant "ClimateView"      as CV   #FCE4EC
participant "ClimateViewModel"  as CVM  #E8F8E8
participant "TemperatureModel\nlv_subject_t" as M #EBF5FB
participant "HomeViewModel"    as HVM  #E8F8E8
participant "HomeView"         as HV   #FCE4EC

== Binding Setup  (once, during buildUi) ==

note over CV, HV #FFE082
  <b>MVVM Binding — LVGL Observer API</b>
  Views call LVGL binding functions on ViewModel's lv_subject_t*.
  LVGL creates lv_observer_t internally, owned by the widget.
  No ConnectionHandle stored — observer lifetime = widget lifetime.
end note

CV  ->  CVM : targetTemperature()
CVM --> CV  : lv_subject_t*
CV  ->  CV  : lv_label_bind_text(tempLabel, subject, "%d°C")

HV  ->  HVM : targetTemperature()
HVM --> HV  : lv_subject_t*
HV  ->  HV  : lv_label_bind_text(tempLabel, subject, "%d°C")\nlv_arc_bind_value(arc, subject)

== Runtime: user increments temperature ==

User -> CV  : tap [+]
CV   -> CVM : increment()
CVM  -> M   : lv_subject_set_int(subject, get() + 1)

group <b>Binding fires</b> — lv_subject_t notifies all widget observers  #FFE082

    M   --> CVM : subject updated
    CVM --> CV  : <b>widget observer</b> → lv_label_set_text(21°C)

    M   --> HVM : subject updated
    HVM --> HV  : <b>widget observer</b> → lv_label_set_text(21°C)\n                   lv_arc_set_value(21)

end

@enduml
